    },
    {
      "text": "Master of Illusion, known in Europe as Magic Made Fun: Perform Tricks That Will Amaze Your Friends! and in Japan as Magic Encyclopedia (マジック大全, Majikku Taizen), is a magic video game developed by Tenyo and Eighting and published by Nintendo for the Nintendo DS. It was released in Japan on November 16, 2006, November 26, 2007 in North America and March 14, 2008 in Europe. Around 9 of its magic tricks were released as separate pieces of DSiWare. It was a collaboration between Nintendo and Japanese magic company Tenyo.\nThe packaging of the game includes a full deck of Nintendo playing cards (manufactured by Tenyo) so the player can practice the card illusions they had learned while playing the game outside of the portable system.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "wikipedia_en"
    },
    {
      "text": "『マジック大全』（マジックたいぜん）は、2006年11月16日に任天堂が発売したニンテンドーDS用ソフトである。マジック用のトランプが付属品として同梱している。\nマジック考案・監修はマジック用品メーカーのテンヨー。",
      "lang": "ja",
      "source": "wikipedia_ja"
    },
    {
      "text": "Faites de la magie est un jeu vidéo sorti sur Nintendo DS le 14 mars 2008 en Europe.\nQuelques mini-jeux ont été repris pour la DSiWare, au prix de 200 Nintendo Points.",
      "lang": "fr",
      "source": "wikipedia_fr"
    }
  ]
